ZH: 我昨天量了一下血压，正常得很。
EN: I measured my blood pressure yesterday, and it was normal.
ZH: 高血压是一种常见的慢性疾病。
EN: Hypertension is a common chronic disease.
ZH: 他最近一直在努力控制血压。
EN: He has been making efforts to control his blood pressure recently.
ZH: 血压的测量是一个重要的健康指标。
EN: Blood pressure measurement is an important health indicator.
ZH: 我们应该经常检查自己的血压。
EN: We should check our blood pressure regularly.
ZH: 他的血压较低，需要特别注意饮食。
EN: His blood pressure is low, so he needs to pay special attention to his diet.
ZH: 血压高可能会增加患心脏病的风险。
EN: High blood pressure may increase the risk of heart disease.
ZH: 长时间的工作压力会导致血压升高。
EN: Long-term work stress can cause an increase in blood pressure.
ZH: 减少盐分的摄入可以帮助降低血压。
EN: Reducing salt intake can help lower blood pressure.
ZH: 运动可以有效地调节血压。
EN: Exercise can effectively regulate blood pressure.
ZH: 高血压患者应该规律地服药。
EN: Patients with hypertension should take medication regularly.
ZH: 血压的波动会受到情绪的影响。
EN: Blood pressure fluctuation can be influenced by emotions.
ZH: 坚持健康的生活方式可以维持正常血压。
EN: Maintaining a healthy lifestyle can help maintain normal blood pressure.
ZH: 血压的正常范围是多少？
EN: What is the normal range for blood pressure?
ZH: 高血压患者需要监测自己的血压水平。
EN: Patients with hypertension need to monitor their blood pressure levels.
ZH: 血压过高可能会引起头痛和头晕。
EN: High blood pressure can cause headaches and dizziness.
ZH: 他的高血压需要长期治疗。
EN: His hypertension requires long-term treatment.
ZH: 不良的饮食习惯会增加血压的风险。
EN: Poor dietary habits can increase the risk of high blood pressure.
ZH: 血压监测仪可以随身携带，方便日常使用。
EN: Blood pressure monitors can be carried around for convenient daily use.
ZH: 血压测试应该在静息时进行。
EN: Blood pressure tests should be done at rest.
